</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[227,1437,564,731]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Apterae 
<quantity box="[326,446,564,590]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.7">0.7–1 mm</quantity>
, shiny red-brown, ochreous or olive brown. Legs and antennae slightly paler. Dorsum reticulate, abdominal mid-dorsum fairly smooth, siphunculi squamose. Siphunculi narrowly conical, slightly dorsoventrally flattened, tapering towards a rounded apex; aperture small, subapical. PT/B = 0.6–1.16; RIV+V/HT2 = 1.2–1.5. Shady broad-leaved, mixed and coniferous forests, mesotrophic meadows. Can be found all year. Monoecious. Not ant-attended.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
